[0.008, "o", "==============================================\r\n  PIHARNESS Demo 5: Orchestrator Supervision\r\n==============================================\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", ">>> What is supervise?\r\n    Wraps a long-running orchestrator task with token-limit\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    monitoring and auto-handoff to the next runtime.\r\n\r\n>>> Command:\r\n    ./piharness.sh supervise \"Build and deploy the app\" --timeout 1800\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n    When the current runtime hits its token limit:\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "      1. State is compacted into a handoff brief\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "      2. Next runtime in chain picks up seamlessly\r\n      3. Runtime chain: pi → opencode → gemini → codex → droid → ollama → claude\r\n\r\n>>> Running a brief supervise session...\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    (limited to 30 seconds for the demo)\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "--- supervise output ---\r\n"]
[0.051, "o", "Cleaned.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "--- end supervise output ---\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", ">>> Auto-handoff preserves:\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    - Current task state and progress\r\n    - Worker relationships and surface IDs\r\n    - Runtime chain position\r\n    - Error history and cooldowns\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n==============================================\r\n  Demo 5 Complete\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "==============================================\r\n"]
